    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka cabinet nod for cost-based cooking gas pricing formula",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s cabinet of ministers has approved a proposal to introduce a cost-based pricing formula for cooking gas that will liquid petroleum (LP) gas prices received once a month.",
        "The proposal, made by President Ranil Wickremesinghe in his capacity as the Minister of Finance, will see gas prices revised on the fifth of every month according to the formula, reflecting cost.",
        "The goal of this decision is to ensure an interrupted supply of domestic gas, a statement from the government information department said on Tuesday August 09. (Colombo/Aug09/2022)"
      ],
